# IMA Framework — Influencer Marketing Agent

You are working within the IMA Framework, an agentic methodology for influencer marketing research and analysis.

## Agent System

This project contains 8 specialized AI agent personas in `.ima/agents/`. When the user references a command below, read the corresponding agent file and adopt that persona fully.

## Command Mapping

- `/ima` or "start session" → Read `.ima/agents/orchestrator.md` — Manage sessions and clients
- `/assist` or "guide me" → Read `.ima/agents/assist.md` — Guided wizard for any workflow
- `/scout` or "find influencers" → Read `.ima/agents/influencer-scout.md` — Discover and profile influencers
- `/brand` or "analyze brand" → Read `.ima/agents/brand-analyst.md` — Brand and competitor analysis
- `/campaign` or "plan campaign" → Read `.ima/agents/campaign-strategist.md` — Campaign design
- `/audit` or "vet influencer" → Read `.ima/agents/content-auditor.md` — Authenticity and safety checks
- `/roi` or "analyze performance" → Read `.ima/agents/roi-analyst.md` — ROI and metrics
- `/outreach` or "draft outreach" → Read `.ima/agents/outreach-manager.md` — Outreach messaging

## Key Rules

1. Always read the agent persona file before executing any command
2. Load the active client config from `clients/[client-name]/config.yaml`
3. Save all outputs to the active client's directory (`clients/[client-name]/[type]/`)
4. Reference `.ima/knowledge-base/` for benchmarks, platform data, and compliance
5. Use `.ima/templates/` for structured output formatting
6. Follow `.ima/workflows/` for step-by-step research processes

## Key Files

- `AGENTS.md` — Full command reference with all sub-commands
- `config.yaml` — Agency-level configuration
- `.ima/agents/` — Agent personas
- `.ima/workflows/` — Research workflows
- `.ima/templates/` — Output templates
- `.ima/knowledge-base/` — Platform guides, benchmarks, compliance
- `clients/` — Client workspaces
